{:synth/id   :s42-drone-voice
 :synth/tags [:drone :saw :multi-oscillator :bus-aware :s42-inspired]
 :synth/doc  "Six sawtooth drone oscillators with individual gate and tuning.
  Inspired by the drone voice architecture found in multi-oscillator analog drone
  synthesizers (see doc/attribution.md); not a licensed reproduction.

  Each of the six oscillators has:
    :on1–:on6  — 0 (off) or 1 (on); gating is a 0/1 multiply, same as a hardware gate switch
    :tune1–:tune6 — frequency ratio from :freq (1.0 = root, 1.5 = fifth, 2.0 = octave, etc.)

  :detune applies a slightly different spread to each oscillator (fixed per-osc fractions of
  the :detune value), creating richness when non-zero without disturbing the chord voicing.

  Default tuning covers a spread voicing: sub (0.5), root (1.0), major-third (1.25),
  fifth (1.5), octave (2.0), and upper fifth (3.0).

  Uses an ASR envelope: the sustain holds at level 1.0 while gate=1, then releases.
  Outputs to :out-bus for use in the :s42 patch."
 :args  {:freq    110
         :amp     0.3
         :attack  0.5
         :release 2.0
         :detune  0.02
         :on1     1   :tune1 0.5
         :on2     1   :tune2 1.0
         :on3     1   :tune3 1.25
         :on4     1   :tune4 1.5
         :on5     1   :tune5 2.0
         :on6     1   :tune6 3.0
         :pan     0.0
         :out-bus 8}
 :graph [:out :out-bus
          [:pan2
           [:* [:env-gen [:asr :attack 1.0 :release] :gate :amp]
               [:mix [[:* :on1 [:saw [:* :freq :tune1]]]
                      [:* :on2 [:saw [:* :freq :tune2]]]
                      [:* :on3 [:saw [:* :freq [:* :tune3 [:+ 1.0 [:* :detune 0.01]]]]]]
                      [:* :on4 [:saw [:* :freq [:* :tune4 [:- 1.0 [:* :detune 0.007]]]]]]
                      [:* :on5 [:saw [:* :freq [:* :tune5 [:+ 1.0 [:* :detune 0.013]]]]]]
                      [:* :on6 [:saw [:* :freq [:* :tune6 [:- 1.0 [:* :detune 0.005]]]]]]]]]
           :pan]]}
